pronunciation: REDOUND, [Latin redundo; red, re, and undo, to rise or swell, as waves.]

definitions.text:
1. To be sent, rolled driven back.The evil, soon driven back, redounded flood on those from whom it sprung.
2. To conduce the consequence; contribute; result.The honor done our religion ultimately redounds God the author of it.
3. To proceed the consequence effect; result.There will no small use redound from them that manufactures.
